    nursingActions: ["Use validated pain assessment tools that capture functional impact, not just pain intensity (BPI, PROMIS, PEG scale: Pain, Enjoyment, General Activity)", "Educate patients on pain neuroscience: understanding central sensitization and that pain does not always equal tissue damage reduces fear-avoidance and catastrophizing", "Monitor opioid agreements: urine drug testing schedule, PDMP checking, pill counts, single prescriber and pharmacy documentation", "Assess for opioid misuse behaviors: early refill requests, escalating doses without provider approval, obtaining opioids from multiple sources, functional decline despite higher doses", "Coordinate multidisciplinary care: physical therapy, behavioral health, pain psychology, complementary medicine referrals", "Educate on safe opioid storage (locked cabinet) and disposal (drug take-back programs, FDA-approved disposal methods)", "Monitor for opioid-induced side effects: constipation (prescribe prophylactic stimulant laxative for all chronic opioid patients), sedation, respiratory depression, hypogonadism, immune suppression", "Assess sleep hygiene and screen for sleep disorders - improving sleep quality significantly reduces pain perception"],
